olive oil
1 Brown Onion
1 beetroot
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet Chicken Drumstick Fillet
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut onion into quarters. Cut beetroot into small chunks.
• Place onion, beetroot and peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven tray.
Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, spread
out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the veggies have 15 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying
pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook boneless chicken drumsticks and Aussie spice blend,
turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 10-14 minutes.

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, combine baby spinach leaves and roasted veggies in a large
bowl.

• Slice spiced chicken.
• Divide roast pumpkin toss between plates. Top with chicken.
• Dollop over dill & parsley mayonnaise. Garnish with crispy shallots to
serve. Enjoy!